caption: b'We know what cats love, and we get excited about offering up new product innovations from all brands within our cat food portfolio, including @meowmix and @nutrish. As part of our Leadership Spotlight series, Rob Ferguson, Senior Vice President and General Manager of Pet Food & Snacks, discusses how we\xe2\x80\x99re continuing to support the health and happiness of cats by offering high-quality products and value. :cat: #SmuckerFam'

b'Virtual interviews have become the norm in this time of social distancing. Our Talent Acquisition team believes in supporting candidates so they can put their best foot forward and has offered tips to help you nail your virtual interview, so you can be the next member of our #SmuckerFam. Check them out at the link in our bio!'
b'Happy Thanksgiving from our #SmuckerFam to yours!'

b'As part of our continued pledge to promote inclusion, diversity and equity at Smucker, we recently welcomed speakers Charmaine Holland and Daniel Juday, who shared their insight with our #SmuckerFam through a virtual discussion focused on unpacking misinformation and meeting others where they are. Special thanks to graphic recorder @justjohnine for capturing the conversation in real-time with this graphic!'

b'Employees across our organization are participating in Smucker Giving Week, an all-virtual event focused on our charitable partners, like the @humanrightscampaign. Our incredible employees continue to amaze us with their philanthropy, and we\xe2\x80\x99re excited to triple their donations during this special event. Thank you, #SmuckerFam, for helping us make a difference!'

b'As part of our Leadership Spotlight series, Vice President of Coffee Research & Development Jim Trout discusses our founding membership with @wcoffeeresearch, a non-profit organization whose research focuses on finding ways for coffee plants to better stand up to disease, drought and environmental challenges.'

b'Our @milkbone brand is proud to sponsor @akronchildrens Doggie Brigade, which brings volunteer dogs around patients to lift their spirits. In light of COVID-19, the hospital moved to virtual or socially-distanced outdoor visits to maintain their support. Thank you to Akron Children\xe2\x80\x99s Hospital for delivering world-class care while recognizing the impact our four-legged friends can have! :dog_face: #smuckerfam'

b'Today, we honor all Smucker veterans and their families for their selflessness and dedication. That selfless devotion is weaved into the fabric of our Company, including our former CEO, Paul Smucker, who spent two years in the Navy. Join us in celebrating the brave men and women nationwide who serve or have served our country.'

b'Our company often says we hire people for a career, not just a job. Kathy Bower, a member of our #SmuckerFam working at our Bloomsburg, PA facility, is a shining example of that. We are delighted to congratulate Kathy on 50 years of service and dedication to producing quality products for pets!'

b'Our @milkbone team is always looking for innovative opportunities to make our treats even more fun. One exciting example is the new customizable boxes, which allow pet parents to add their furry family member\xe2\x80\x99s name and picture to the front of the box! Visit the Milk-Bone website to learn more :dog_face: #smuckerfam'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to be recognized as one of America\xe2\x80\x99s Best Employers for Women. The annual list developed by @forbes is based on feedback from employees on their own companies and others they hold in high regard. #americasbestemployersforwomen'

b'Nursing home residents have been among the most impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic. Recognizing this, our Away From Home team developed kits with games and activities to share with residents to pick up their spirits, and have distributed more than 35,000 to date. Thanks to the #smuckerfam behind this thoughtful initiative to support a unique need created by the pandemic.'

b'During the challenging times we face, simple reminders of the beauty around us are especially important. This spirit inspired the Cleveland Orchestra to create the Beethoven 9 Project, featuring a performance of Beethoven\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cOde to Joy\xe2\x80\x9d filmed at 16 iconic locations around Greater Cleveland. We are proud to support @cleveorch and pleased to share this optimistic message that highlights the unique community we have called home for more than 120 years. :red_heart_selector::musical_note:'

b'On #WorldFoodDay and every day, we\xe2\x80\x99re proud to match our employees\xe2\x80\x99 generous donations to partners like @feedingamerica, @acrfoodbank and @greatergoodcharities\xe2\x80\x99 Rescue Bank to help fight hunger for people and pets. #smuckerfam'

b'This week, our team members across the country gathered virtually to connect, share stories and sip on @cafebustelo in celebration of #hispanicheritagemonth. This bold, vibrant brand is rich with Latino history and is the perfect way to celebrate. \xc2\xbfQuieren m\xc3\xa1s? Check out three Latin-inspired mixes by searching Caf\xc3\xa9 Bustelo on Spotify. :yellow_heart::hot_beverage: #smuckerfam'

b'Our people are passionate about helping others. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we asked employees to nominate charities for our Company Matching Gift Program, which doubles employee impact by matching donations dollar for dollar. Read more about the winning charities and our Charitable Giving efforts at jmsmucker.com. #smuckerfam'

b'This #InternationalCoffeeDay we celebrate smallholder green coffee farmers around the world, like Pak Ngaturining from Indonesia. As the leader in U.S. at-home coffee, it\xe2\x80\x99s our responsibility to help provide the training and resources farmers like Pak need to thrive. Learn how we partner with @hrnstiftung to achieve this by visiting the link in our bio. #smuckerfam'

b'#nationalcoffeeday is our kind of holiday :hot_beverage: Smucker coffees are brewed in more American homes than any other company. Celebrate the day with your favorite roasts and flavors from Folgers, Dunkin\xe2\x80\x99 and Caf\xc3\xa9 Bustelo #smuckerfam #butfirstcoffee:hot_beverage:'

b'Things will look a little different around here starting today! We\xe2\x80\x99ve evolved our identity to better reflect the tremendous growth you\xe2\x80\x99ve helped us experience the last two decades. Go behind the scenes to learn more about this important effort by visiting www.jmsmucker.com! #smuckerfam'

b'We recently achieved a significant milestone toward our goal of 10% greenhouse gas emissions intensity reduction by 2020 with the completion of Plum Creek wind farm! The farm is expected to produce enough renewable energy credits to match 50% of our total electricity usage annually. Thank you to our partners @orstedus for their work on this project #smuckerfam'
b'Our @jifbrand team has spent years ensuring new Jif Squeeze delivers the same Jif taste and texture peanut butter lovers crave. Look for it on shelves near you! #smuckerfam #peanutbutter'

b'This year\xe2\x80\x99s summer internship program was unlike any other given the pandemic. We\xe2\x80\x99re incredibly proud of the flexibility and commitment displayed by our all-star intern class and our #SmuckerFam for continuing to make the program a success.'
b'We\xe2\x80\x99re joining the #StopHateForProfit movement because it\xe2\x80\x99s important for us to act on our values. Learn more via the link in our bio.'

b'On the 51st anniversary of the Stonewall Uprising, we listen, learn and love as members of and allies to the LGBTQ+ community. Read about what #Pride means to our #SmuckerFam at jmsmucker.com #SpreadtheLove #PrideMonth'

b'Our President and CEO, Mark Smucker, recently signed the CEO Action for Diversity & Inclusion pledge, which further reflects our commitment to real, meaningful and sustained action to ensure a more inclusive workplace, while supporting greater cultural awareness and sensitivity in our communities. To learn more about this commitment, visit ceoaction.com. More info on the additional work we\xe2\x80\x99re doing as an organization to play an even stronger role in the fight against racial injustice can be found at jmsmucker.com'

b'The calls for change being shouted across our country must continue. We want the Black community to know we hear you, we\xe2\x80\x99re with you and we\xe2\x80\x99re determined to be a part of real, meaningful and sustained change to end racial injustice. To read our CEO\xe2\x80\x99s message to employees, which includes specific ways we\xe2\x80\x99re taking action, visit jmsmucker.com'

b'To help maintain our commitment to continuous learning while social distancing, we\xe2\x80\x99ve recently launched a program called Peer Connections. These virtual sessions include open dialogue so employees can interact from afar while focusing on renewal, self-awareness and well-being. #smuckerfam #mycompany #workfromhome #wellness'

b'We have big news for cat parents :cat: \nAfter identifying a need for treats that combine great taste, quality ingredients and engaging textures, our @nutrish team launched a new line purrfect for snack time! Check them out at nutrish.com'

b':honeybee: #WorldBeeDay is the perfect time to get into the garden! Our very own Pollinator Garden, located in our hometown of Orrville, OH, is maintained with the help of employee volunteers and knowledge from @pollinatorpartnership. As pollinators, bees are essential to our planet\xe2\x80\x99s food supply. To learn about how you can help, visit pollinator.org :honeybee:'

b'We want to continue fostering the sense of community that makes our culture unique for our employees working remotely. In that spirit, we\xe2\x80\x99ve created the Better Together community - a virtual gathering place that is 1,300 employees strong which provides educational tools and resources to support physical and mental health. #smuckerfam #mycompany #stayhealthy'

b'We are so proud of our dedicated employees in New Orleans for supporting local heroes and the area economy. Our team members partnered with @unitedwaysela to provide 2,500 meals from area restaurants to local EMS professionals working tirelessly on the front lines of the COVID-19 pandemic. #smuckerfam #supporthealthcareheroes'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been humbling to hear from employees who want to support their coworkers facing unexpected financial hardships. To assist, we established the Smucker Employee Relief Fund, making it easy for employees to contribute or apply for a hardship grant. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to provide an initial contribution of $100,000 and have committed to matching all employee donations dollar for dollar. #smuckerfam #wereinthistogether'

b'Our partners at @unitedway are one of the leading supporters of #givingtuesdaynow, which aids the emergency response to the need created by COVID-19. To join us in supporting this cause, visit givingtuesday.org \n#givingtuesday #smuckerfam #mycompany'

b'In the midst of providing humanitarian support to communities most impacted by COVID-19, @americanredcross is reminding all that \xe2\x80\x9cemergencies don\xe2\x80\x99t take a break.\xe2\x80\x9d We are very proud to support the organization\xe2\x80\x99s continued efforts to provide food, shelter and care for those impacted by emergencies of all sizes. #smuckerfam #mycompany'

b'Thank you to our manufacturing professionals in Sherbrooke, QC, for their dedication in delivering a steady supply of Carnation:registered_selector: and Eagle Brand:registered_selector: canned milk products to meet consumer demand in grocery stores across Canada in this time of need. We appreciate all that you do! #smuckerfam #mycompany'

b'Our Orrville campus dining hall is equipped with Grind2Energy:trade_mark_selector:, which transforms food scraps into a clean, renewable source of energy, supporting our continued commitment to sustainability. :recycling_symbol_selector: #smuckerfam #sustainability #earthweek :globe_showing_Americas:'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re incredibly excited about the progress being made on the Plum Creek Wind Project in Wayne County, NE! Once completed, Plum Creek will produce enough renewable energy certificates annually to match 50 percent of our total electricity usage. Thanks to our partners at @orstedus for their efforts! #smuckerfam #earthday2020 #windenergy #earthday'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI hold my grandfather, Paul, as one of the best examples of how to be a good human being. He was very loving, and incredibly kind. He always saw the good in others and treated everyone he came across with respect and compassion. He was a tremendous leader, particularly in challenging times like we\xe2\x80\x99re experiencing now. He used his sense of humor to remind us to not over complicate, but take pride in our business of making and selling food that would delight consumers. I am incredibly grateful for the time we got to spend together and hold those memories close, especially today, his birthday.\xe2\x80\x9d - Mark Smucker, President and CEO'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re so proud of our employees in Longmont, CO, who helped our facility win Food Engineering Plant of the Year! Their significant efforts getting the plant up and humming help provide even more Uncrustables to families across the country. #smuckerfam #mycompany'

b'Our partners at @feedingamerica continue to step up for the people impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic. Their work includes launching a national COVID-19 response fund to support those in need, partnering with school districts and local government agencies to provide continued meal access to 22 million children and working with local governments to support federal nutrition programs in their emergency response plans. Thank you for everything you do - we\xe2\x80\x99re proud to partner with you! :folded_hands: \n#smuckerfam #mycompany'
b'Thank you to our partners at the @acrfoodbank who continue to go above and beyond to provide food to those in need during these challenging times :flexed_biceps: \n#smuckerfam #mycompany'
b'Our routines may have gone to the dogs (and cats), but the light provided by our furry companions-turned-coworkers shines brighter than ever before :red_heart_selector: #smuckerfam #mycompany'
b'To the 5,000+ women and men on the ground at our facilities working to keep our nations fed - THANK YOU :red_heart_selector:'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cLearning to see the world through my son\xe2\x80\x99s eyes has been an incredibly rewarding experience and an unexpected journey of self-discovery and personal growth.\xe2\x80\x9d -Bruce Davis, Senior Corporate Counsel, The J.M. Smucker Company\n#autismawarenessmonth #celebratedifferences #smuckerfam #mycompany'

b'People have always, and will continue to, come first at our company. It\xe2\x80\x99s why we announced several new measures today to support our #smuckerfam employees, including COVID-19 related pay and benefits continuation, paid leave and a financial award. Full details at the link in our bio.'
